ads/2012/12/graduation.png\" /></a></div>','Graduation','','publish','closed','closed','','graduation','','','2018-11-07 01:29:29','2018-11-07 01:29:29','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=124',1,'portfolio-piece','',0),(125,1,'2012-12-11 23:24:43','2012-12-11 23:24:43','','graduation','','inherit','open','open','','graduation','','','2012-12-11 23:24:43','2012-12-11 23:24:43','',124,'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/graduation.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(79,1,'2012-12-04 05:20:21','2012-12-04 05:20:21','<p>Our challenge for this application was to create our own paint program from scratch. The catch was that we were not allowed to use any sort of traditional painting tools. Pen, brush, line, box, were all out of the question. I decided to create a program in which the user can draw different nature scenes. His tools are elements of Mother Nature. His palette is the seasons. The application may have trouble running in your browser--you must have Java installed. If you can\'t run it, click <a title=\"Painting Nature Application\" href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/PaintNatureApplication.zip\">here</a> to download the file to run it locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a title=\"Painting Nature Application\" href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/portfolio-piece/painting-nature-application/\">Click here to try it out!</a>\r\n\r\nHere are some examples of scenes created with the program:</p>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/painting-nature-1.jpg\"><img class=\"center size-full wp-image-106\" title=\"Painting Nature Nighttime Scene\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/painting-nature-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"676\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/painting-nature-2.jpg\"><img class=\"center size-full wp-image-107\" title=\"Painting Nature Springtime Scene\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/painting-nature-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" /></a>','Painting Nature','','publish','closed','closed','','painting-nature','','','2018-04-24 20:07:44','2018-04-24 20:07:44','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=79',15,'portfolio-piece','',0),(80,1,'2012-12-04 05:19:10','2012-12-04 05:19:10','','Painting Nature','','inherit','open','open','','painting-nature-2','','','2012-12-04 05:19:10','2012-12-04 05:19:10','',79,'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/painting-nature.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(81,1,'2012-12-04 05:23:05','2012-12-04 05:23:05','<iframe class=\"margin-bottom-small\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/29696046?badge=0\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"800\" height=\"540\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThe song, called Star of Wonder by Sufjan Stevens, I thought runs deeper than only the music and could be improved by visual aid. I thought of what the song might mean, what it tries to communicate, and what that might look like on a screen. I tried to listen more closely to the music and really focus on what images the music builds in my mind. When shooting the video, I tried to elaborate on some of the themes that the music touches on such as: the smallness or insignificance of human beings, the aesthetics of lights, the stars and the moon, the busyness of our lives and how small and insignificant we are, and the overall awesomeness and grandeur of the Universe. I shot within the city and let the bigness of the city parallel and serve as a metaphor with the theme of the hugeness of the Universe.\r\n\r\nSince I was not able to get any shots of the night sky in detail with the primitive equipment that I have, I let the city lights serve as a substitute. I made sure that the rhythm of the video matches the rhythm of the music, such as only cutting on beat with the music or the stop motion segments alongside the fleeting sounds of the flute and keyboard. Segments with quicker tempoed sounds match with quicker movements on the screen, and more peaceful music match with serene landscapes or sights of lights. I tried to focus on the framing and color of the shots in the video the most. With all of the city lights, the colors are very important. Additionally, the camera movement provided another hugely important element in the video, which offers different artistic perspectives in the way the images are presented.','Star of Wonder','','publish','closed','closed','','star-of-wonder','','','2019-08-21 21:42:48','2019-08-21 21:42:48','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=81',16,'portfolio-piece','',0),(82,1,'2012-12-04 05:23:19','2012-12-04 05:23:19','','Star of Wonder','','inherit','open','open','','star-of-wonder-2','','','2012-12-04 05:23:19','2012-12-04 05:23:19','',81,'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/star-of-wonder.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(83,1,'2012-12-04 05:24:28','2012-12-04 05:24:28','Problem statement:\r\n\r\n<p><em>Using the elements of design covered in class, create a final version of your personal poster. Look for ways to modify and refine the composition and typography. Expand beyond the grayscale color palette of your first poster. Develop the formal elements of the poster, both the graphical elements within the page and the size and shape of the entire poster (minimum size of 16\" x 16\"). Sharpen the conceptual approach of your project.</em></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Since the poster was supposed to display our most important hopes and desires, I tried to communicate the idea that sometimes those who are the most important to us and the most dear to us are those that hurt us the most. This idea represents a very stark contrast of emotions and therefore I had to be careful as to balance those emotions equally.</p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/poster2.png\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/poster2.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"Personal Poster 2.0\" width=\"784\" height=\"1000\" class=\"center size-full wp-image-116\" /></a>','Personal Poster 2.0','','publish','closed','closed','','personal-poster-2-0','','','2018-04-24 20:11:05','2018-04-24 20:11:05','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=83',17,'portfolio-piece','',0),(84,1,'2012-12-04 05:24:12','2012-12-04 05:24:12','','Personal Poster 2.0','','inherit','open','open','','poster-2','','','2012-12-04 05:24:12','2012-12-04 05:24:12','',83,'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/poster-2.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(85,1,'2012-12-04 05:26:13','2012-12-04 05:26:13','Problem statement:\r\n\r\n<p><em>A connection between postmodernism and poststructuralism is a shift from a single, authoritarian voice to multiple perspectives. In postmodernism, this shift manifests itself in a hybrid aesthetic. Poststructuralism emphasizes the importance of identity in interpretation; it posits a person\'s gender, race, sexuality, class, ethnicity, and age affect viewpoint.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>For this second assignment, develop a multi-page project that modifies a traditional myth, legend, fable or fairy tale through the filters of postmodernism and poststructuralism. For example, you could change the gender, race or sexuality of a myth\'s main character. You could make marginal characters the main characters. You could alter the location and era of the text. You could mix the narrative structure with new narratives or create a narrative that presents multiple perspectives. Look for ways to alter your myth/legend/fable/fairy tale, connecting it to your life and interests.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Expand upon the design elements and principles you incorporated in your poster. Emphasize the visual aspects of your narrative; look for inspiration in graphic novels and film storyboards. Issues of image-making, framing and composition come to the fore. And since this is a multi-page project, consciously consider issues of sequencing and timing.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The myth I chose to modify is the fable of the city mouse and the country mouse. While the city mouse is always busy, the country mouse has a very slow and modest life. Unlike this myth, mine comes to a slightly different conclusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"view-narrative\" href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg1.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\">view narrative</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg2.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg2.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg3.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg3.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg4.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg4.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg5.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg5.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg6.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg6.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg7.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg7.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg8.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg8.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg9.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg9.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg10.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg10.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg11.jpg\" rel=\"shadowbox[david]\" class=\"center\">\r\n	<img style=\"display: none; height: 1px;\" src=\"http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/resources/david/pg11.jpg\" alt=\"David\" />\r\n</a>','Narrative: A Modern Myth','','private','closed','closed','','narrative-a-modern-myth','','','2018-11-07 01:27:18','2018-11-07 01:27:18','',0,'http://jrstrauss.net/portfolio-new/?post_type=portfolio-piece&#038;p=85',18,'portfolio-piece','',0),(86,1,'2012-12-04 05:25:58','2012-12-04 05:25:58','','David','','inherit','open','open','','david','','','2012-12-04 05:25:58','2012-12-04 05:25:58','',85,'http://portfolio.jrstrauss.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/david.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(87,1,'2012-12-04 05:34:29','2012-12-04 05:34:29','','Crawford Media Services','','private','closed','closed','','crawford-media-services','','','2013-05-24 21:07:15'